Usage: addRoutingHalo [-help] [-orientation <string>] { {-bottom <auto|name> -space <left bottom right top> -top <auto|name>} | -lithoHalo } {-allBlocks  | -block <name> | -cell <name> | -inst <name> | -designHalo  }

-help                              # Prints out the command usage
-allBlocks                         # for all blocks (bool, required)
-block <name>                      # block names (list, required)
-bottom <auto|name>                # bottom layer name (string, required)
-cell <name>                       # cell names (list, required)
-designHalo                        # for all partitions (bool, required)
-inst <name>                       # instance names (list, required)
-lithoHalo                         # adds a litho halo to the instances on each
                                   # routing layer with LEF LITHOMACROHALO
                                   # defined (bool, required)
-orientation <string>              # base on orientation (string, optional)
-space <left bottom right top>     # space on 4 sides (list, required)
-top <auto|name>                   # top layer name (string, required)